Program: The History Hour
Title: The Good Friday Agreement
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswql7
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 1 Apr 2018
In 1998, the political parties in Northern Ireland reached a peace agreement that ended decades of war. We hear from Paul Murphy, the junior minister for Northern Ireland at the time. Plus, a cross-community choir in Bosnia and women pioneers from the worlds of finance and oceanography. PHOTO: Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern (L) and British Prime Minister Tony Blair (R) pose with the mediator Show less